g.text: It is well known that WPSH is a strongest subtropical anticyclone high pressure system controlling monthly
weather conditions in YRD during late-summer and may intensify in a warming climate background. To
systemically study the impact of WPSH on inter-annual variability of ozone pollution in Shanghai under
the climate change background, intensive surface measurements of ozone and meteorological data and the
